'''Rachel Chagall''' (born '''Rachel Levin'''; 24 November 1952) is an [[United States|American]] [[actress]], best known for roles as Gaby<ref>http://tcm.tv/this-month/article.html?isPreview=&id=499692|218343&name=Gaby-A-True-Story</ref> in the film ''[[Gaby: A True Story]]'' (1987), for which she was nominated for [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actress – Motion Picture Drama]], and as [[Val Toriello]] on ''[[The Nanny (TV series)|The Nanny]]'' (1993–1999).
==Life and career== Chagall was born in [[New York City]],<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0106080/trivia ''The Nanny (TV Series): Trivia''; imdb.com]</ref><ref>[http://www.yatedo.com/p/Rachel+Chagall/famous/ae119ddfc5f5b0f930043cbb8cca1604 Chagall's biography at Yatedo.com]</ref> to a [[Jews|Jewish]] family.<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0106080/trivia ''The Nanny (TV Series): Trivia''; imdb.com]</ref><ref>[http://www.yatedo.com/p/Rachel+Chagall/famous/ae119ddfc5f5b0f930043cbb8cca1604 Chagall's biography at Yatedo.com]</ref> In 1982, she contracted [[Guillain–Barré syndrome]], recovering sufficiently to be cast in the starring role of Gaby, A True Story.<ref>http://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/167892.php</ref><ref>http://www.sonymoviechannel.com/movies/gaby-true-story/details</ref>
She is perhaps best known for her role as the dimwitted sidekick, [[Val Toriello|"Val"]], on the 1990s [[United States|American]] television series ''[[The Nanny (TV series)|The Nanny]]''.
She made guest appearances on ''[[Just Shoot Me!]]'' and ''[[Strong Medicine]]''. She also played a mysterious woman in ''[[What I Like About You (TV series)|What I Like About You]]''. As Rachel Levin, Chagall appeared in ''[[Gaby: A True Story]]'' (1987) in the title role as [[Gabriela Brimmer]] (for which she was nominated for a [[Golden Globe]] - Best Actress in a Motion Picture - Drama)<ref>imdb.com, [https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0149575/awards Awards for Rachel Chagall]</ref> and ''[[White Palace (film)|White Palace]]'' (1990) in the role of Rachel. She also appeared in ''[[The Last Supper (1995 film)|The Last Supper]]'' (1995). On December 6, 2004, Chagall appeared at the cast reunion for ''[[The Nanny (TV series)|The Nanny]]'', ''[[The Nanny Reunion: A Nosh to Remember]]''.
